==English==
===Etymology===
Borrowed from Latin '''inferior''', the comparative of '''infra''', meaning "low"

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪəriə(r)|-ɪəriə(r)]]

===Adjective===
'''inferior'''
#of lower [[quality]]
#of lower rank
#In [[botany]], inside the flower stalk below the [[petal]]s. Said of an [[ovary]].

===Noun===
'''inferior'''
# a person of lower [[stature]] to another

====Antonym====
*[[superior]]

